FBIS3-38140 "drweu020_j_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Jan 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Andreatta Urges Croatia To Condemn Journalists Murders LD2901185294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1800 GMT 29 Jan 94 LD2901185294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] "Italy is once again confronted with the tragic death of some of its citizens in the territory of the former Yugoslavia. This time they were carrying out their duty of reporting, which is something very important in the framework of the tragic crisis in Bosnia," Foreign Minister Beniamino Andreatta has written to his Croatian counterpart Mate Granic. Andreatta said that he is certain "that the Croatian Government too will condemn this execrable incident" and that all the parties involved will contribute without reservation to ascertaining responsibility.
